Brazil Government ‘Doesn’t Like’ Oil Tax Increase Proposal

-- B y   P e t e r   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-09-15T13:42:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/brazil-government-doesn-t-like-oil-tax-increase-proposal.html
Brazil ’s government “doesn’t
like” a proposal to extend an oil tax to about 300 fields that
are currently exempt, Energy Minister Edison Lobao said today at
an event in Rio de Janeiro.  Paulo Teixeira, leader of President Dilma Rousseff’s
Workers’ Party in the lower house, said yesterday Lobao and
lawmakers had discussed the plan among various proposals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
